{
  "texts": [
    "Upon entering the study, participants completed a reappraisal training that was adapted from two previous studies in which the training helped participants produce effective reappraisals and reduced negative emotions in a large international sample (Pinus et al., 2025; Wang et al., 2020).",
    "After completing the training, participants were asked EXPLORING HUMAN AND AI EMOTIONAL SUPPORT to rate and reappraise nine vignettes in the same format as the practice trial.",
    "At the conclusion of the trials, participants completed a few global measures including life satisfaction, depression symptoms, and reappraisal habits (see Supplementary Materials for full description).",
    "After we collected participants' reappraisals, we reduced the initial set of 18 vignettes and their respective human reappraisals to six, for the sake of generating human ratings (two of each of sadness, anxiety, and anger) while using the remaining 12 vignettes for the purpose of fine-tuning a LLM.",
    "We focused on six reappraisals because we hoped to acquire 50 ratings per reappraisal, which would result in an infeasible sample size for all 18 vignettes."
  ]
}